      • setRenderMode

        public void setRenderMode(GLViewHolder.RenderMode renderMode)
        Description copied from interface: GLViewHolder
        Set the rendering mode. When GLViewHolder.RenderMode is RENDER_CONTINUOUSLY, the renderer is called repeatedly to re-render the scene. When GLViewHolder.RenderMode is RENDER_WHEN_DIRTY, the renderer only rendered when the surface is created, or when GLViewHolder.requestRender() is called. Defaults to RENDER_CONTINUOUSLY.
        Specified by:
        setRenderMode in interface GLViewHolder
        Parameters:
        renderMode - one of the GLViewHolder.RenderMode enums
